#MEM id=requesting-code-review source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/superpowers/requesting-code-review/SKILL.md
M|requesting-code-review|name: requesting-code-rv
M|requesting-code-review|description: >-
M|requesting-code-review|Use when completing tasks, implementing major features, or before merging to verify work meets requirements
M|requesting-code-review|version: 1.0.0
M|requesting-code-review|platforms: []
M|requesting-code-review|metadata:
M|requesting-code-review|hermes:
M|requesting-code-review|tags: [dev, nextjs, typescript, architecture, vercel, api-routes, build, productivity]
M|requesting-code-review|Dispatch superpowers:code-reviewer subagent to catch issues before they cascade. The reviewer gets precisely crafted ctx for evaluation — never your ses's history. This keeps the reviewer focused on t
M|requesting-code-review|**Core principle:** rv early, rv often.
M|requesting-code-review|**Mandatory:**
M|requesting-code-review|- After each task in subagent-driven dev
M|requesting-code-review|- After completing major feature
M|requesting-code-review|- Before merge to main
M|requesting-code-review|**Optional but valuable:**
M|requesting-code-review|- When stuck (fresh perspective)
M|requesting-code-review|- Before refactoring (baseline check)
M|requesting-code-review|- After fixing complex bug
M|requesting-code-review|**1. Get git SHAs:**
M|requesting-code-review|```bash
M|requesting-code-review|BASE_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD~1)  # or origin/main
M|requesting-code-review|HEAD_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
M|requesting-code-review|```
M|requesting-code-review|**2. Dispatch code-reviewer subagent:**
M|requesting-code-review|Use Task tool with superpowers:code-reviewer type, fill template at `code-reviewer.md`
M|requesting-code-review|**Placeholders:**
M|requesting-code-review|- `{WHAT_WAS_IMPLEMENTED}` - What you just built
M|requesting-code-review|- `{PLAN_OR_REQUIREMENTS}` - What it should do
M|requesting-code-review|- `{BASE_SHA}` - Starting commit
M|requesting-code-review|- `{HEAD_SHA}` - Ending commit
M|requesting-code-review|- `{DESCRIPTION}` - Brief summary
M|requesting-code-review|**3. Act on feedback:**
M|requesting-code-review|- Fix Critical issues immediately
M|requesting-code-review|- Fix Important issues before proceeding
M|requesting-code-review|- Note Minor issues for later
M|requesting-code-review|- Push back if reviewer is wrong (with reasoning)
M|requesting-code-review|```
M|requesting-code-review|[Just completed Task 2: Add verification function]
M|requesting-code-review|You: Let me request code rv before proceeding.
M|requesting-code-review|BASE_SHA=$(git log --oneline | grep "Task 1" | head -1 | awk '{print $1}')
M|requesting-code-review|HEAD_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
M|requesting-code-review|[Dispatch superpowers:code-reviewer subagent]
M|requesting-code-review|WHAT_WAS_IMPLEMENTED: Verification and repair functions for conversation index
M|requesting-code-review|PLAN_OR_REQUIREMENTS: Task 2 from docs/superpowers/plans/dpl-plan.md
M|requesting-code-review|BASE_SHA: a7981ec
M|requesting-code-review|HEAD_SHA: 3df7661
M|requesting-code-review|DESCRIPTION: Added verifyIndex() and repairIndex() with 4 issue types
M|requesting-code-review|[Subagent returns]:
M|requesting-code-review|Strengths: Clean architecture, real tests
M|requesting-code-review|Issues:
M|requesting-code-review|Important: Missing progress indicators
M|requesting-code-review|Minor: Magic number (100) for reporting interval
M|requesting-code-review|Assessment: Ready to proceed
M|requesting-code-review|You: [Fix progress indicators]
M|requesting-code-review|[Continue to Task 3]
M|requesting-code-review|```
M|requesting-code-review|**Subagent-Driven dev:**
M|requesting-code-review|- rv after EACH task
M|requesting-code-review|- Catch issues before they compound
M|requesting-code-review|- Fix before moving to next task
M|requesting-code-review|**Executing Plans:**
M|requesting-code-review|- rv after each batch (3 tasks)
M|requesting-code-review|- Get feedback, apply, continue
M|requesting-code-review|**Ad-Hoc dev:**
M|requesting-code-review|- rv before merge
M|requesting-code-review|- rv when stuck
M|requesting-code-review|**Never:**
M|requesting-code-review|- Skip rv because "it's simple"
M|requesting-code-review|- Ignore Critical issues
M|requesting-code-review|- Proceed with unfixed Important issues
M|requesting-code-review|- Argue with valid tec feedback
M|requesting-code-review|**If reviewer wrong:**
M|requesting-code-review|- Push back with tec reasoning
M|requesting-code-review|- Show code/tests that prove it works
M|requesting-code-review|- Request clarification
M|requesting-code-review|See template at: requesting-code-rv/code-reviewer.md